page.title: 18Local organizations
page.content: The local organizations in Maple Cross are Brownies,Guides and Cubs.Brownies and guides are on a Friday.{Brownies is from 5.30pm until 7.00pm.{Guides is from 7.00pm until 9.00pm.{Cubs}are on a Tuesday from 6.00pm until 7.00pm At{guides}we do all sorts of things, for example,we went for a fry_up in the woods and other weeks we have just stayed in the hut and played games. The{brownies}uniform is a brown woolen hat with a brown bobble on the top,a brown dress,a yellow tie,a silver enrollment badge (that goes on the tie) and a brown belt and purse. The{guide}uniform is a navy blue skirt,a blue blouse,a navy blue hat,a maroon tie and a gold enrollment badge. Both groups have badges that identify what patrol they are in and if they are a sixer or patrol leader
